narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I had never taken a theory course that was as rigorous as professor Cohn's meter seminar. It was an incredibly difficult class for me but I was able to throw myself into the depths of theoretical rhetoric in a way that I had not engaged with before this semester.
Facility with certain analytic tools, a vocabulary to talk about the temporal aspects of music, and a good number of metric and rhythmic hors-d'oeuvres to fool around with in the brain.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I felt totally overwhelmed at the beginning of the semester and felt that I had to work very hard to catch up to my peers. That said, once things clicked about mid-semester I felt that my understanding of the course material grew exponentially in a very short period of time.

I found the course strong. I don't have much constructive criticism. I guess I'll just say that I always lobby for greater number of musical examplespunctuating classroom talk with actual music helps me learn, and always helps me bring it back to the real topic at hand.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes absolutely but I would make sure to let them know that the theoretical background required to comprehend the reading should not be taken lightly
